This paper deals with the issue of fairness in algorithmic decision-making, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the temporal aspect of fairness, which involves the timing of decisions, and this could potentially fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or cryptography (cs.CR) since these fields deal with the security and privacy of data. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for fair decision-making, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) since it involves designing algorithms that take into account the social implications of their decisions.
